482
00:31:12,604 --> 00:31:13,696
Fine.

483
00:31:30,955 --> 00:31:33,253
Who's gonna get the light, Ava?

484
00:31:43,434 --> 00:31:45,698
Okay. Time to wake up.

485
00:31:47,906 --> 00:31:49,567
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

486
00:31:49,674 --> 00:31:52,006
And here. Practice your Spanish.

487
00:31:54,445 --> 00:31:56,913
I am so glad I rescued my dress.

488
00:31:59,851 --> 00:32:02,251
To have lost it would have been a tragedy.

489
00:32:02,353 --> 00:32:03,877
Tell me about it.

490
00:32:03,988 --> 00:32:07,754
I have no idea what I'm gonna wear
to the party. I have no clothes!

491
00:32:08,192 --> 00:32:09,955
Yes, you do!

492
00:32:10,061 --> 00:32:14,020
I still have the hand-me-downs
you gave me for the church drive.

493
00:32:14,465 --> 00:32:17,957
There are not too many homeless
that are size 2, anyway.

494
00:32:18,970 --> 00:32:21,404
Okay. I'm done here. I'm leaving.

495
00:32:21,506 --> 00:32:24,270
- Where are you going?
- Yogalates.

496
00:32:24,976 --> 00:32:28,036
And then I'm off to Sassy Maids
to see if they'll take me back

497
00:32:28,146 --> 00:32:31,673
after all these years.
Some of us have to work for a living.

498
00:32:31,783 --> 00:32:36,243
Oh, and girls, please behave.
Don't burn down the house.

499
00:32:36,888 --> 00:32:38,753
Lock the door. See you later.

500
00:32:41,960 --> 00:32:45,293
Do you remember this? This was yours.
Do you want it back?

501
00:32:46,230 --> 00:32:47,356
No.

502
00:32:49,434 --> 00:32:50,401
Not bad.

503
00:32:52,503 --> 00:32:53,470
Cute.

504
00:32:57,408 --> 00:32:58,375
Kids.

505
00:33:03,948 --> 00:33:05,643
I feel so last year.

506
00:33:05,750 --> 00:33:08,344
Calm down. Retro's really in right now.

507
00:33:11,089 --> 00:33:13,387
Hi. It's the red Mercedes.

508
00:33:14,525 --> 00:33:17,551
- What do I look like, a valet?
- Yes.

509
00:33:17,662 --> 00:33:20,654
Honey, there's no valet here.

510
00:33:39,851 --> 00:33:42,786
Oh, God. I'm God's personal joke.

511
00:33:44,956 --> 00:33:48,016
I think he said we need to get on the 2

512
00:33:49,060 --> 00:33:51,324
and then switch to the 37.

513
00:33:52,430 --> 00:33:56,526
And then on the 6. On the 6!

514
00:33:56,634 --> 00:33:58,864
Just like J. Lo.

515
00:34:01,439 --> 00:34:02,531
And then...

516
00:34:02,640 --> 00:34:05,803
And then we gotta get on the 2,
but a different 2 than the first 2.

517
00:34:05,910 --> 00:34:09,402
This is ridiculous.
Somebody has gotta come pick us up.

518
00:34:09,914 --> 00:34:13,873
You're right. You know, friends don't
let friends take public transportation.

519
00:34:13,985 --> 00:34:16,715
Especially the bus. Ava.

520
00:34:16,821 --> 00:34:20,052
I've heard about the bus.
People pee on the seats.

521
00:34:20,158 --> 00:34:23,127
- Tanzie. They don't pee on the bus.
- They pee.

522
00:34:27,098 --> 00:34:30,499
<i>Yo, it's Mic. Tune in Wednesday night.</i>
<i>Wait for the beep.</i>

523
00:34:30,601 --> 00:34:34,196
Mic! Baby, it's Avie. Where are you?

524
00:34:34,739 --> 00:34:38,231
What's going on? I mean,
I've called you, like, a million times.

525
00:34:38,576 --> 00:34:41,374
We're announcing our engagement
in, like, two hours.

526
00:34:42,213 --> 00:34:43,805
Call me, call me, call me. Okay?

527
00:34:43,915 --> 00:34:46,406
But don't worry about Tanz and I.
We're on our way.

528
00:34:46,517 --> 00:34:50,351
Our ride just got here. Bye. Love you.

529
00:34:54,025 --> 00:34:56,585
- Lady.
- What?

530
00:34:56,694 --> 00:34:59,060
I'm not tipping you
till I know how your service is.

531
00:34:59,163 --> 00:35:02,826
It's $1.35 each.

532
00:35:03,568 --> 00:35:05,798
- Fine.
- I've got change.

533
00:35:12,076 --> 00:35:15,603
- We're going to 273 Benedict Canyon.
- Good for you.

534
00:35:20,184 --> 00:35:21,242
Excuse me.

535
00:35:31,229 --> 00:35:33,493
Why do they have to start like that?

536
00:35:34,799 --> 00:35:36,994
- It smells in here.
- I know.

537
00:35:39,237 --> 00:35:41,967
Hey! I could feel that.

538
00:35:42,406 --> 00:35:43,373
Oh, my God.

539
00:35:44,408 --> 00:35:47,605
Excuse me. I am not God's personal joke.

540
00:35:47,778 --> 00:35:49,712
I'm his entire comedy routine.

541
00:35:49,814 --> 00:35:52,578
That's why in Japan,
women have their own buses.

542
00:36:07,431 --> 00:36:09,695
Wait, wait! This isn't Benedict Canyon!

543
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:12,735
- Where are you going?
- No tip for you!

544
00:36:14,872 --> 00:36:17,636
Why aren't there any sidewalks?

545
00:36:20,077 --> 00:36:23,171
Ava, I can't do this anymore.
I've got blisters.

546
00:36:23,281 --> 00:36:26,409
- And I didn't even really wanna come.
- Tanzie?

547
00:36:27,218 --> 00:36:29,686
This is
my engagement announcement party.

548
00:36:29,787 --> 00:36:31,812
Everybody already knows you're engaged.

549
00:36:31,923 --> 00:36:34,255
I mean, they knew when you started
wearing that promise ring

550
00:36:34,358 --> 00:36:36,622
and saying you guys were just friends.

551
00:36:38,963 --> 00:36:39,930
Come on.

552
00:36:40,965 --> 00:36:41,932
Ow.

553
00:36:50,274 --> 00:36:53,505
Yeah, all right.
I'll take care of that. Yeah.

554
00:36:53,611 --> 00:36:55,408
- Hi.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

555
00:36:57,815 --> 00:37:01,444
- It's Ava and Tanzie Marchetta.
- I'm sorry, you're not on the list.

556
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:05,721
I am Mic's fiancée, okay?
I wrote the freaking list.

557
00:37:05,823 --> 00:37:08,451
It's Marchetta. With an M.
You know, like Manila.

558
00:37:08,559 --> 00:37:09,651
Yeah, I know who you are.

559
00:37:09,760 --> 00:37:11,751
My mama used to like
to wear your lipstick.

560
00:37:11,862 --> 00:37:15,855
Yeah, but I bet if she had the same skin
shade as you, she'd like the raspberry.

561
00:37:15,967 --> 00:37:18,959
Mama died last year.
Maybe now I know why.

562
00:37:20,171 --> 00:37:24,574
Do you know how mad Mic is gonna be
when he finds out how you treated us?

563
00:37:24,709 --> 00:37:28,236
- You're done. He is gonna be so pissed.
- Look! Look, it's Etienne.

564
00:37:28,713 --> 00:37:32,774
- Etienne! Etienne, hey! Etienne!
- He can't hear you.

565
00:37:39,357 --> 00:37:40,722
- Go!
- Etienne, it's us.

566
00:37:40,825 --> 00:37:43,919
We're outside,
and this guy isn't letting us in.

567
00:37:44,161 --> 00:37:49,030
Actually, I decided not to go to the party
because my throat is a little tender.

568
00:37:49,133 --> 00:37:52,227
Turn around.
I am looking at you on the patio.

569
00:37:52,336 --> 00:37:53,826
That's not me.

570
00:38:00,411 --> 00:38:03,812
- We're being totally dissed.
- By Etienne?

571
00:38:03,914 --> 00:38:06,041
- Yeah.
- He worships us.

572
00:38:06,150 --> 00:38:08,084
- Well.
- He was gonna go straight for us.

573
00:38:08,185 --> 00:38:09,914
You know what?
He's not straight for us anymore.

574
00:38:10,021 --> 00:38:11,682
And you know what?
Etienne's not even Brazilian!

575
00:38:11,789 --> 00:38:16,055
- Ava!
- Sol! Thank God.

576
00:38:16,160 --> 00:38:18,458
I know, baby, I know.

577
00:38:18,562 --> 00:38:20,826
We've been on this bus,
and we've been hiking around.

578
00:38:20,931 --> 00:38:23,627
And then this guy won't even let us in!

579
00:38:23,734 --> 00:38:25,702
Just take me to go and see Mic.

580
00:38:25,803 --> 00:38:28,363
Yeah, actually,
that won't be happening now.

581
00:38:28,839 --> 00:38:32,036
As his agent,
I have to look after Mic's best interests.

582
00:38:32,143 --> 00:38:37,046
And the thing is, <i>Long Island</i> is
about to squeak into the top ten.

583
00:38:37,615 --> 00:38:41,881
Let's face it. You're a liability now.
So, as far as the engagement goes,

584
00:38:42,353 --> 00:38:44,548
I think we're gonna have to pass.

585
00:38:44,722 --> 00:38:49,455
Pass? What are you saying?
Are you dumping me?

586
00:38:49,560 --> 00:38:52,586
Well, technically,
Mic's dumping you. Look.

587
00:38:52,697 --> 00:38:54,858
I have to think long-term,
and a career choice like...

588
00:38:54,965 --> 00:38:56,364
Okay. Right.

589
00:38:57,468 --> 00:39:01,529
From a business standpoint, you know,
I get where you're coming from, okay?

590
00:39:02,340 --> 00:39:05,969
But look, on the other hand,
this was my engagement day,

591
00:39:06,677 --> 00:39:08,474
and I risked my life to save this dress.

592
00:39:08,579 --> 00:39:12,015
So, you know
what you can tell your client? Karma!

593
00:39:12,116 --> 00:39:15,483
- I'll let him know. And one other thing.
- What?

594
00:39:15,586 --> 00:39:17,554
We're gonna need the ring back.

595
00:39:24,228 --> 00:39:28,722
You know what else?
<i>Long Island</i> is a really bad show!

596
00:39:29,467 --> 00:39:31,162
- I hate it.
- This is a disaster.

597
00:39:31,535 --> 00:39:34,595
Our sales have plummeted
precipitationally.

598
00:39:34,705 --> 00:39:38,664
And the retailers have already returned
almost 90% of our shipments.

599
00:39:40,511 --> 00:39:42,911
- Hi.
- Hi.

600
00:39:46,817 --> 00:39:48,478
Hi. Sorry.

601
00:39:48,586 --> 00:39:52,386
Jaden, for heaven's sake,
get them a moist towel or something.

602
00:39:54,225 --> 00:39:56,489
- What's going on?
- Carry on.

603
00:39:56,894 --> 00:39:59,260
Carry on. Yes, well.

604
00:40:00,097 --> 00:40:01,997
Fabiella did make us an offer.

605
00:40:02,533 --> 00:40:06,435
It was lower than we hoped for,
but in light of present circumstances...

606
00:40:06,537 --> 00:40:08,232
How much is it for?

607
00:40:09,907 --> 00:40:11,636
How much is it for?

608
00:40:12,777 --> 00:40:14,802
Sixty cents on the dollar
for all our private stock.

609
00:40:14,912 --> 00:40:16,277
Sixty cents?

610
00:40:16,380 --> 00:40:20,214
It's actually quite generous.
I mean, it could go down again next week.

611
00:40:20,751 --> 00:40:21,718
What?

612
00:40:24,455 --> 00:40:27,686
If we sell to Fabiella,
what happens to the Marchetta name?

613
00:40:28,459 --> 00:40:30,927
If we're lucky, we disappear quietly.

614
00:40:32,129 --> 00:40:34,859
Quietly disappear?
What about your investigation?

615
00:40:34,965 --> 00:40:37,559
Well, I looked into the Everdew file...

616
00:40:38,536 --> 00:40:39,662
Thank you, Pam.

617
00:40:41,705 --> 00:40:44,071
And I don't know how to tell you this,

618
00:40:44,175 --> 00:40:47,201
but there were some problems
in the testing stage.

619
00:40:47,344 --> 00:40:52,441
And your father, for whatever reason,
decided not to deal with it.

620
00:40:53,451 --> 00:40:56,545
What he's saying
is that the complaints are legit.

621
00:40:56,654 --> 00:40:57,951
I'm sorry, girls.

622
00:40:59,023 --> 00:41:02,288
But, Tommy, you're not just gonna, like,
accept this, right?

623
00:41:02,393 --> 00:41:06,352
I mean, you're gonna track down
those people from the story.

624
00:41:06,464 --> 00:41:10,093
Yes, yes. I'm gonna try.
I threatened to sue.

625
00:41:10,201 --> 00:41:13,898
- But Nakamori won't give up his sources.
- People, can we pick up the pace here?

626
00:41:14,004 --> 00:41:16,598
Yes. All right, let me be frank here.

627
00:41:18,142 --> 00:41:21,509
This company was already a sinking ship.

628
00:41:21,612 --> 00:41:25,605
With this new publicity scandal,
we're the <i>Titanic.</i>

629
00:41:26,584 --> 00:41:28,677
It's disfortunate but true.

630
00:41:29,887 --> 00:41:34,620
And this is an excellent opportunity
for the shareholders to save their hides.

631
00:41:35,025 --> 00:41:36,720
It's a great opportunity.

632
00:41:38,395 --> 00:41:39,760
I gotta pee.

633
00:41:42,266 --> 00:41:43,733
Yeah. Thanks.

634
00:41:44,401 --> 00:41:46,232
Thank you for sharing.

635
00:41:49,540 --> 00:41:53,101
Oh, my God. I am a federal emergency.

636
00:41:53,210 --> 00:41:56,270
- No wonder Mic dumped me.
- What are we doing in here, Ava?

637
00:41:56,380 --> 00:41:59,372
I don't know.
I just needed a second to think.

638
00:42:00,251 --> 00:42:03,379
Well, come on! Let's just go in there
and vote to sell this stupid company

639
00:42:03,487 --> 00:42:08,618
- that Dad totally screwed up.
- Hey, look, Daddy wasn't perfect, okay,

640
00:42:08,859 --> 00:42:11,851
but getting things right
was so important to him.

641
00:42:11,996 --> 00:42:15,432
- What do you mean?
- I don't know. I haven't figured it out yet,

642
00:42:17,468 --> 00:42:20,494
but I know I want
to get my hands on those test files.

643
00:42:21,505 --> 00:42:25,874
We vote no. We don't believe our father
is guilty of any wrongdoing.

644
00:42:26,143 --> 00:42:30,273
The board doesn't need your votes to
pass this. Now, let's get this thing done.

645
00:42:30,514 --> 00:42:32,505
I've got a plane to Maui in an hour.

646
00:42:32,616 --> 00:42:35,346
All those in favor of bringing this offer
to the stockholders for approval

647
00:42:35,452 --> 00:42:37,750
with our recommendation to sell?

648
00:42:43,294 --> 00:42:45,922
- I'm going to exstain.
- Yes.

649
00:42:46,030 --> 00:42:49,227
I will see you all in 30 days
at the stockholders' meeting.

650
00:42:50,834 --> 00:42:51,801
You...

651
00:43:01,378 --> 00:43:03,312
Can I get a statement?
When can I get a statement?

652
00:43:03,414 --> 00:43:06,349
Hey, hold back!
Come on, come on, come on! Step back!

653
00:43:06,884 --> 00:43:08,681
Please, people. Step back.

654
00:43:10,254 --> 00:43:13,382
Sir, if you could step back
just a couple of feet. Just stay back. Guys!

655
00:43:13,490 --> 00:43:15,185
There they are.

656
00:43:30,040 --> 00:43:31,701
What do I press?
Come, follow me.

657
00:43:31,809 --> 00:43:34,209
- Four, three, two, one.
- Ava, come on.

658
00:43:34,311 --> 00:43:37,109
This is Brad Tibe at E! and I'm actually
following the Marchetta sisters

659
00:43:37,214 --> 00:43:39,512
right here in downtown Los Angeles!

660
00:43:40,851 --> 00:43:42,113
Come on. Hurry.

661
00:43:45,856 --> 00:43:47,881
- Ava.
- I think it's broken.

662
00:43:47,992 --> 00:43:49,550
You have to leave it.

663
00:43:50,928 --> 00:43:51,952
- No.
- Leave it.

664
00:43:52,062 --> 00:43:53,290
- No.
- Yes.

665
00:43:58,535 --> 00:44:00,332
- Rick.
- Get in.

666
00:44:00,437 --> 00:44:02,837
Can I get
a statement from you?

667
00:44:02,940 --> 00:44:05,534
- Is it true your cosmetics cause cancer?
- No.

668
00:44:05,643 --> 00:44:08,373
Come on! Give me an E! exclusive!

669
00:44:13,817 --> 00:44:15,512
It should be on the left.

670
00:44:23,193 --> 00:44:24,956
Thanks.
You're welcome.

671
00:44:25,062 --> 00:44:26,029
Yeah.

672
00:44:27,564 --> 00:44:29,054
It's so windy.

673
00:44:32,770 --> 00:44:33,964
- Thanks.
- Sure.

674
00:44:41,912 --> 00:44:45,143
Rick, you were amazing.

675
00:44:45,883 --> 00:44:47,612
We owe you bigtime.

676
00:44:48,285 --> 00:44:50,082
And I never welch on a debt,

677
00:44:51,488 --> 00:44:54,082
despite what you might read
in the papers.

678
00:44:54,191 --> 00:44:56,751
Don't worry. I'll collect on that later.

679
00:44:57,594 --> 00:45:00,563
And I never believe
what I read in the papers.

680
00:45:00,664 --> 00:45:01,756
Good.

681
00:45:12,242 --> 00:45:13,300
Bye.

682
00:45:19,983 --> 00:45:21,610
Jeez. Tanz.

683
00:45:23,153 --> 00:45:26,088
- He's a parking attendant.
- He's cute.

684
00:45:37,134 --> 00:45:38,999
Los Angeles Free Legal Clinic.

685
00:45:39,970 --> 00:45:41,961
Hi. Remember us?

686
00:45:44,241 --> 00:45:46,971
Can we have a word with you
in your office?

687
00:45:48,112 --> 00:45:49,636
You're looking at it.

688
00:45:49,747 --> 00:45:52,045
